JOHANNESBURG –The price of petrol and diesel are set to drop on 7 February 2018. The Energy Department says a stronger Rand is the main contributor to the price decrease, as it's countered the rising cost of brent crude oil. READ: Slight petrol price relief expected for new year Motorists will pay 30c less for petrol, and 17c less for diesel, per litre. The price of illuminating paraffin is expected to drop by 19-cents per litre. eNCA